         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">11/2/95 ¶  ¶ Best thanks, highly esteemed Professor, for the last list of names of algae that have been given immediately to Miss Hussey and Mr O'Halloran. ¶  ¶ It is very pleasing that you remain rob...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">95.02.11</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Jacob Agardh</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Handskr. Avdl., Universitetsbibliotek, Lund, Sweden.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">11/2/95</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Besten Dank, hochgeehrter Herr Professor, für die letzten Namenslisten der Algen, welche sogleich Miss Hussey und Mr O'Halloran mitgetheilt sind</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es ist recht erfreulich, dass Sie kräftig bleiben, um so rüstig fortarbeiten zu können</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich sende heute wieder Algen von Miss Hussey ab. Es sind manche gewöhnliche dabei, (<name key="Codium">Codium</name>, <name key="Chrysymenia">Chrysymenia</name> &amp;c) aber ich halte es doch am Besten alles abzusenden an Sie, schon der additionellen Localitäten wegen.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wäre es möglich einen <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Census</hi>
               </seg> der Algen Australiens nach der Form meines Census der Vascular-Pflanzen zusammengestellt zu bekommen? Es würde die Übersicht so erleichtern beim Gebrauch der Exemplare.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Lake</hi>
               </seg> Macquarie ist im subtropischen Ost Australien. Ich habe besondere Anstrengungen gemacht von dort Algen zu erlangen denn dort hört die südliche Algenflora schon auf. Es ist eben aus diesem Grunde, dass ein Census, welcher so leicht auszuarbeiten wäre, erschiene, um so die geographische Verbreitung recht clar<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">klar?</p>
               </note> zu machen. Ihnen wird mein Census in Lund zugänglich sein.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Sie ehrend der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">In einem Census könnten Sie ja auch Ihre neueste Auffassung der Genera u Arten entwickeln —</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">11/2/95</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Best thanks, highly esteemed Professor, for the last list of names of algae that have been given immediately to Miss Hussey and Mr O'Halloran.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter and lists not found.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is very pleasing that you remain robust to be able to continue to work so actively.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Today I am again sending algae from Miss Hussey. There are several common ones among them (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Codium">Codium</name>
               </seg>, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Chrysymenia">Chrysymenia</name>
               </seg>&amp;c) but I do regard it best to send everything to you, already on account of additional localities.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would it be possible to get compiled a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Census</hi>
               </seg> of the algae of Australia after the form of my census of vascular plants?<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B<seg style="">83.03.04, second edition B89.02.03. </seg>
                     <seg style="">in c.1883 M had prepared a manuscript including algae in the style of </seg>B<seg style="">83.03.04 but it was never published: see n. 4 in M to W. Mitten, 22 November 1881 (in this edition as 81-11-22a).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> It would make the overview so much easier in use of specimens.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Lake</hi>
               </seg> Macquarie<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">NSW.</p>
               </note> is in subtropical east Australia. I have made particular efforts to obtain algae from there, because there the southern algal flora terminates. It is just for this reason that a census, which would be so easy to prepare, should appear to make the geographical distribution very clear. My census will be available to you in Lund.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Esteeming you your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">In a census you could certainly also develop your latest concept of genera and species —<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The postscript is written in the margins; there is no space below the valediction.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Codium">Codium</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Chrysymenia">Chrysymenia</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
